# PHP Coding Style Rules

## No Constructor Property Promotion

Do not use PHP 8.0+ constructor property promotion syntax. Always declare class properties explicitly in the class body and assign them in the constructor.

### Bad (do not use):

```php
class Example
{
    public function __construct(
        private readonly string $state,
        private readonly array $children,
        private readonly int $offset,
    ) {}
}
```

### Good (use this style):

```php
class Example
{
    private readonly string $state;

    private readonly array $children;

    private readonly int $offset;

    public function __construct(
        string $state,
        array $children,
        int $offset,
    ) {
        $this->state = $state;
        $this->children = $children;
        $this->offset = $offset;
    }
}
```
